headline: Three Reasons Why CHRW is Risky and One Stock to Buy Instead
summary: C.H. Robinson Worldwide has had an impressive run over the past six months as its shares have beaten the S&P 500 by 7.7%. The stock now trades at $103.51, marking a 17% gain. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
